P664.label: organizer
P664.description: person or institution organizing an event

P710.label: participant
P710.description: person, group of people or organization that actively takes/took part in the event

P832.label: public holiday
P832.description: official public holiday that occurs in this place in its honor, usually a non-working day

P1110.label: attendance
P1110.description: number of people (spectators, ticket holders) at an event or exhibition

P1446.label: number of missing
P1446.description: number of people missing after an event - qualify with "point in time (P585)"

P1478.label: has immediate cause
P1478.description: nearest, proximate thing that directly resulted in this outcome or effect. Used in conjunction with 'has cause' (i.e. underlying cause) and 'has contributing factor'. See 'Help:Modeling causes'.

P1479.label: has contributing factor
P1479.description: thing that significantly influenced, but did not directly cause, this outcome or effect.  Used in conjunction with 'has cause' and 'has immediate cause'.  See 'Help:Modeling causes'.

P1534.label: end cause
P1534.description: qualifier to use together with the end date qualifier (P582) to specify the cause

P1535.label: used by
P1535.description: item that makes use of the subject (use sub-properties when appropriate)

P1537.label: contributing factor of
P1537.description: thing that is significantly influenced by this cause, but does not directly result from it.  See 'Help:Modeling causes' for examples and discussion.

P276.label: location
P276.description: location the item, physical object or event is within.  In case of an administrative entity use P131. In case of a distinct terrain feature use P706.

P726.label: candidate
P726.description: person or party listed as an option for office in an election

P1111.label: votes received
P1111.description: number of votes for a candidate in an election
